metatags.og:title: Surface mites in dogs, cats and rabbits
metatags.og:description: Mites are small arthropods with a world-wide distribution. They can be parasitic or free-living. Some burrow into the skin of pet animals or live in their hair follicles, while others can be found on the surface of the skin and/or ear. Clinical signs of infestation in dogs, cats and rabbits are variable. Infestations are typically diagnosed by skin scrapings, coat brushings, hair plucks, and tape strips. Readily available veterinary insecticidal products are often effective but may need to be combined with environmental control procedures.
